reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Whole food vitamin that's fully packed
reviews.reviewText: I like this product because it has a lot of variety of things that the body needs as well as some wonderful superfoods. I didn't really realize how iron deficient I was until I started taking these. I have increased energy and focus. Plus I like vitamins that are not a solid chalk type pill but are actual capsules with powdered ingredients. It doesn't take the body all day to break down and process.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars As with all supplements…
reviews.reviewText: This particular multivitamin may have not agreed with me & that could’ve been for a number of reasons, interaction with current medications or supplements, body, etc.. As with anything we decide to intake, if on medication having your physician take a glance at what we’re planning on adding doesn’t hurt. Two things I can say is that, 1st the shipping was fast, bottle clean, vitamins green (not the most pleasant taste, not end of the World) & 2nd the customer service was great, so very pleasant.. I contacted them as per the instructions & received a callback the very next morning. Thank you.P.S. Considering trying one without iron, might work better, as suggested.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Well Balanced Vitamins
reviews.reviewText: I like the effect of these vitamins, they're jam packed with micro and micronutrients that the body needs. I also like that they have probiotics as well. The only thing I don't love is the taste, they're very garlicky tasting but nothing a drink can't handle. Also, for those who are wondering, yes the veggies and probiotics do increase your uh...bowel activity. Lots of gas and a VERY regular schedule. I originally didn't make the connection but everytime I stop taking them and restart, I'm super gassy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Worked for years until now it doesn't
reviews.reviewText: I have used these vitamins for years with good results, until my last couple orders. My husband complained that they bothered his stomach & I just assumed that was just him being overly sensitive. After all, I've taken them (at only 1 a day for years, and both my daughter & I took them through the pandemic with general health improvement. I skip taking them from time to time, but have always got back into the habit because I felt better on them until... this last batch. There has always been color differences between batches, but this time I think whatever made the change effected me poorly. While it's entirely possible my own health has changed (I've always had a bit of a sensitive gut - but these were helping it for years!) now I can't take one without having problems. I've tried holding my other supplements and only taken this one (Others included: a probiotic, Mg, Zinc, Vit B, & Vit E & occasional iron - all of which served me well alongside this MVI until recently), tried going off this one completely, tried just taking my other supplements, & tried other multi-vitamins. And... it's this multivitamin. When I am off it, my gut issues resolve. As soon as I add it back in my gut rebels. I thought it was something else for months, but no. I'm super sad because it worked so well for so long. Now I need to find something else. I get stupid cravings & generalized fatigue without a multi
